ARCHITECTURAL PRESERVATION LICENSE v1.0
========================================

Copyright (c) 2025 Brian Thorne

PREAMBLE
--------

This license governs the Universal Life Protocol (ULP) v1.1 implementation and
its sealed architecture. The purpose is to ensure the Five Immutable Principles
remain intact while allowing modification, distribution, and commercial use.

DEFINITIONS
-----------

"Software" refers to the ULP v1.1 implementation, including but not limited to:
  - Core utilities (bin/ directory)
  - World definition files (world/ directory)
  - Interrupt handlers (interrupts/ directory)
  - Documentation (all .md, .txt files)
  - Architecture specification (ULP-v1.1-ARCHITECTURE.txt)

"Architecture" refers to the sealed v1.1 specification with hash:
  9872936e788b17f2b2114565b2af789350ea3e155e93ee0ce5cb1f656c5a57fd

"Five Principles" refers to:
  1. Trace is Append-Only and Authoritative
  2. World Definition is Non-Executable
  3. Projections are Pure Functions
  4. Effects are Forward-Only via .interpose
  5. Information Flows Forward-Only

"Derivative Work" means any modification, extension, or translation of the
Software that retains compatibility with the Architecture.

"Breaking Change" means any modification that violates one or more of the Five
Principles.

