Subject to the following conditions:

CONDITIONS
----------

1. ARCHITECTURAL PRESERVATION

   Any Derivative Work that claims compatibility with "ULP v1.1" MUST:

   a) Preserve all Five Principles without exception

   b) Maintain the authority hierarchy:
      Trace > World Definition > Projections > Effects

   c) Respect closed vocabulary sets:
      - 13 world file types (sealed)
      - 16 trace event types (sealed)
      - 13 effect symbols (sealed)
      - 16 projection classes (sealed)

   d) Reference the Architecture hash in all traces:
      9872936e788b17f2b2114565b2af789350ea3e155e93ee0ce5cb1f656c5a57fd

2. BREAKING CHANGES

   Any modification that violates the Five Principles is a Breaking Change and:

   a) MUST be released under a new major version (v2.0+, not v1.x)

   b) MUST NOT claim compatibility with "ULP v1.1"

   c) MAY use the name "ULP" but MUST clearly indicate incompatibility:
      Examples: "ULP v2.0 (incompatible with v1.1)"
                "Modified ULP (non-standard)"

   d) SHOULD document which principles were changed and why

3. ATTRIBUTION

   All copies and Derivative Works MUST include:

   a) This LICENSE file (unmodified)

   b) Copyright notice: "Copyright (c) 2025 Brian Thorne"

   c) A clear statement of any modifications made

   d) If distributed in binary form, the above notices must appear in
      documentation and/or other materials provided with the distribution

4. ARCHITECTURE SPECIFICATION

   The file ULP-v1.1-ARCHITECTURE.txt is the canonical specification.

   a) This file MUST be included unmodified in all distributions claiming
      "ULP v1.1" compatibility

   b) Its SHA-256 hash MUST remain:
      9872936e788b17f2b2114565b2af789350ea3e155e93ee0ce5cb1f656c5a57fd

   c) Alternative architectures are permitted but must use different version
      numbers and filenames (e.g., "ULP-v2.0-ARCHITECTURE.txt")

5. TRACE VALIDITY

   All traces produced by the Software claiming "ULP v1.1" compatibility MUST:

   a) Include the Architecture hash in #METADATA:
      #METADATA architecture_hash 9872936e788b17f2b2114565b2af789350ea3e155e93ee0ce5cb1f656c5a57fd

   b) Follow the trace format specification exactly

   c) Be deterministically reproducible (same inputs → same trace)

   d) Support self-encoding (trace contains complete execution environment)

6. PATENT GRANT

   Each contributor grants a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free
   patent license under the contributor's essential patent claims to make, use,
   sell, offer for sale, import and otherwise run, modify and propagate the
   Software, subject to these conditions.

